The paper discusses motion planning for Micro Aerial Vehicles (MAVs), which is a topic that falls under the field of robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of search-based planning, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper addresses the issue of planning safe trajectories in the presence of motion uncertainty, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of field-of-view constraints, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of motion primitives, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG).
